- 'listed on the NASDAQ exchange' refers to stocks that are traded on the NASDAQ stock market.

- The composite score is calculated as (average return * 0.4) + (news count * 0.3) + (buy rating * 0.3);
- A higher score indicates a more promising stock, considering both performance and market sentiment;
